### Post 5 — [2026, date unknown]
**URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/posts/nickfromseattle_ive-lost-count-of-how-many-seo-audits-ive-activity-7468318501146030081-2AlO


I've lost count of how many SEO audits I've opened to find the same thing.

Bottom-funnel pages picked off a keyword tool, written in isolation, none of them ranking.

A multi-brand reseller showed us their site last month. Their previous agency had written ten bottom-funnel pieces and there was no logic connecting any of them.

The pages were live. Nothing was ranking. And when we looked at the engagement data, it was obvious why.

The handful of people landing weren't staying.

No second page view. No CTA click. No product view.

Engagement metrics tell you early, long before the rankings do, whether the content is going to work. Bounce on arrival means it won't.

What we'd have done instead: pick the two brands they could actually dominate. Build the cluster around each one.

Supporting content, comparisons, the things someone researching that specific brand needs before they buy. Earn authority in a narrow vertical first. Then, once that's locked in, go after the category-level terms everyone wants.

The previous agency didn't fail because they wrote bottom-funnel content. They failed because they wrote ten disconnected pieces and called it a strategy.

Bottom-funnel without topical concentration is just expensive content that doesn't rank.


